{"title_page": "Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker", "text_new": "[[File:Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker.jpg|right|thumb|Kai the hitchhiker describes his hatchet-wielding attack as a \"Smash, Smash, SUH-MASH\".]]\n\n'''''Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker''''' is an internet [[viral video]] featuring a [[Hitchhiking|hitchhiking man]] who calls himself \"Kai\". It was released on February 2, 2013, by a reporter from a local news station in California. The video went viral and received national attention in the press.<ref>{{cite web |last=Thomas |first=Sophie Saint |date=May 16, 2013 |title=Catching Up with Kai, the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker |work=[[Vice News]] |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/catching-up-with-kai-the-hatchet-wielding-hitchhiker |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref> Kai Lawrence, later identified as '''Caleb Lawrence McGillvary''' from Canada, would cite the fall-out from the video as part of his defense against a homicide charge that was filed in New Jersey a few months after the video was released.<!-- The article is about the video not McGillvary. Excessive detail in the lead section about him or the court case will be removed. -->  \n\n==Viral video==\nThe video is by local Fox affiliate [[KMPH-TV|KMPH]] in [[Fresno, California]]. It is an eyewitness account by a man calling himself \"Kai\" who describes what happened (according to Kai) soon after the course of events and while still on the scene. Kai had been hitchhiking and was picked up by a man named Jett Simmons McBride<ref>{{cite web |last1=Campbell |first1=Andy |title=Jett Simmons McBride Claimed To Be Jesus, Attacked Driver, Thwarted By Hitchhiker With Hatchet: Cops |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/04/jett-simmons-mcbride-jesus-hatchet-bear-hug_n_2616737.html |website=[[Huffington Post]] |accessdate=14 October 2018}}</ref> who weighed 300 pounds and claimed to be [[Jesus|Jesus Christ]]. McBride told Kai he once raped a 14-year-old girl in the [[Virgin Islands]] while on a business trip. McBride then crashed into a pedestrian, pinning him against a truck. Kai jumped out of the car to help the pinned pedestrian while the driver remains in the car. However, when a bystander arrived on the scene to help, McBride jumped out and attacked her in a bear hug. Sensing the woman's life may be in danger, and believing the man could snap her neck \"like a pencil stick\", Kai removed a [[hatchet]] from his backpack and began to repeatedly strike McBride in the back of the head. After the hits, McBride staggered away and began masturbating at a nearby school before the police arrive and take the man into custody. Kai described the hatchet-wielding attack as a \"Smash, Smash, SUH-MASH\" while he reenacted the over-head swings.  Kai is interrogated by police and set free.\n\nThe video was uploaded to YouTube on February 2, 2013, by Jessob Reisbeck who also conducted the interview for KMPH.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ckfBGdZoR_0 Kai, Hatchet Wielding Hitchhiker, Amazing Interview w/ Jessob Reisbeck ]  [[YouTube]]</ref> As of October 27, 2019, the video had over 7 million views. [[The Gregory Brothers]] sampled the interview and turned it into a song, as of October 27, 2019, the video garnered over 10 million views.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wDQTvuP1Dgs smash, Smash, SMASH!] on [[YouTube]]</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, McBride was convicted of assault with a deadly weapon and the jury ruled him to be insane, meaning any sentence would be served in a mental hospital and not prison.<ref>https://abc30.com/archive/9383501/</ref><ref>https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/california/jury-finds-man-insane-in-2012-attack-of-pge-worker/71208/</ref>\n\n==Murder conviction==\nSAVE KAI!! He should not be in prison he is a hero #SAVEKAI\nKai was arrested on murder charges in May 2013 for the death of New Jersey attorney Joseph Galfy. Kai maintained he fought against Galfy in self-defense. According to Kai, Galfy attempted to rape him after offering Kai a place to stay for the night. Kai stated that the police claimed the sexual encounter was consensual and the murder premeditated; however, Kai said that after the viral video in California, he had no need to have sex with men like Galfy, who Kai described as unattractive, stating \"Do you know how many hot chicks\u2014never mind. Even if I was gay, do you know how many hot guys wanted to fuck me after that shit in California? I'm not even being vain. It's just a fact, like\u2014no offense, but he [Galfy] was not a looker\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Kavanaugh |first=Shane Dixon |date=July 14, 2016 |title=The Sad Tale Of Kai The Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker |work=ocativ.com |url=http://www.vocativ.com/335097/kai-the-hatchet-wielding-hitchhiker/ |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter the murder charges, the video views increased substantially increasing its viral reach.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rose |first=Lisa |date=May 22, 2013 |title=Parents of Kai the Hitchhiker say the Union Co. murder suspect has had behavioral issues for years |work=nj.com |url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2013/05/mysterious_hitchhiker_from_can.html |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref> Fans of the video, who considered Kai a hero for saving the woman, raised a legal fund.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pearson |first=Michael |date=May 19, 2013 |title=Murder charge stuns some fans of 'Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker' |work=[[CNN]] |url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/17/justice/new-jersey-hitchhiker-charge/ |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |agency=AP |date=May 18, 2013 |title='Hatchet hitchhiker' arrested in US murder |work=[[USA Today]] |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/05/18/hatchet-hitchhiker-arrested-in-us-murder/2268985 |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author= |date= |title=Hatchet-wielding hitchhiker an internet sensation  arrested for murder of NJ man |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/75949340-157.html |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Abad-Santos |first=Alexander |date=May 17, 2013 |title=Couch-Surfing on Viral Video Fame, 'Hatchet Hitchhiker' Arrested for Murder |work=[[The Atlantic]] |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2013/05/couch-surfing-viral-video-fame-hatchet-hitchhiker-was-arrested-murder/315159/ |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gabbatt |first=Adam |date=May 17, 2013 |title='Hatchet-wielding hitchhiker' arrested in {{sic|Philadephia|hide=yes}} on murder charge |work=[[The Guardian]] |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/may/17/hatchet-hitchhiker-arrested-murder |accessdate=April 22, 2017}}</ref> Kai was imprisoned for over five years awaiting trial which began April 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fresnobee.com/news/local/article213123609.html |title=Five years ago, he was 'Kai, the hatchet-wielding hitchhiker.' Now he'll be tried for murder |work=[[The Fresno Bee]] |author=Joshua Tehee |date=June 14, 2018 |accessdate=October 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Haydon |first=Tom |date=May 12, 2016 |title=3 years and counting; no trial yet for jailed YouTube star 'Kai the Hitchhiker' |work=nj.com |url=http://www.nj.com/union/index.ssf/2016/05/kai_the_hitchhiker_wages_legal_battle_from_jail_fi.html |accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref> Kai took the stand in his own defense and was combative during cross examination; he made an outburst during his defense lawyers closing arguments nearly leading to his expulsion from the court room.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nj.com/union/2019/04/kai-the-hitchhiker-found-guilty-of-beating-73-year-old-nj-man-to-death.html |title=\u2018Kai the Hitchhiker\u2019 found guilty of beating 73-year-old N.J. man to death |work=NJ.com |author= Sophie Nieto-Munoz | |date=April 24, 2019 |accessdate=April 24, 2019}}</ref> A jury found him guilty of first-degree murder and he was sentenced to 57 years in prison. He will serve 85 percent of that term before the possibility of parole, with the judge telling McGillvary, \"when you become eligible for parole, you will still be younger than Mr. Galfy was when you murdered him,\" who was 73 at the time.<ref>{{cite web |title=Former Internet Star \u2018Kai The Hitchhiker\u2019 Found Guilty Of Murder |url=https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2019/04/24/former-internet-star-kai-the-hitchhiker-found-guilty-of-murder/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kai-the-hitchhiker-caleb-mcgillvary-sentenced-to-57-years-beating-death-today-2019-05-30/|title=\"Kai the Hitchhiker\" sentenced to 57 years in lawyer's beating death |website=www.cbsnews.com |language=en-US| access-date=2019-05-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mycentraljersey.com/story/news/crime/2019/05/30/kai-hitchhiker-gets-57-year-prison-term/1286476001/ |title='Kai the hitchhiker' gets 57 year prison term for killing Clark attorney |author=Suzanne Russell |via=mycentraljersey.com |work=Bridgewater Courier News |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=May 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ckfBGdZoR_0 Kai, Hatchet Wielding Hitchhiker], YouTube video\n\n[[Category:2013 in California]]\n[[Category:Viral videos]]\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LTUop2vf--M\n", "text_old": "[[File:Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker.jpg|right|thumb|Kai the hitchhiker describes his hatchet-wielding attack as a \"Smash, Smash, SUH-MASH\".]]\n\n'''''Kai the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker''''' is an internet [[viral video]] featuring a [[Hitchhiking|hitchhiking man]] who calls himself \"Kai\". It was released on February 2, 2013, by a reporter from a local news station in California. The video went viral and received national attention in the press.<ref>{{cite web |last=Thomas |first=Sophie Saint |date=May 16, 2013 |title=Catching Up with Kai, the Hatchet-Wielding Hitchhiker |work=[[Vice News]] |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/catching-up-with-kai-the-hatchet-wielding-hitchhiker |